> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Peel @garlic{1%clove}; place whole clove in the center of a small piece of
#foil{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{1%tablespoon} and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Cinch into a packet. Trim and halve @Brussels sprouts{8%ounce}
lengthwise. Dice @fingerling potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Thinly slice
@chives{1/4%ounce}.

Place garlic foil packet on a #baking sheet{}.

Roast on middle rack for ~{10%minutes}, then add Brussels sprouts to same sheet.
Carefully toss with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Return to middle rack until garlic is softened and Brussels sprouts are browned
and tender, ~{15-20%minutes} more.

Meanwhile, place potatoes in a large #pot{} with enough salted water to cover by
2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender when pierced with a fork,
~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.
Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Stir in @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon},
half the chives, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Add reserved potato cooking liquid a
splash at a time as needed until potatoes are creamy.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, pat @bavette steak{10%ounce} very dry with
#paper towels{}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add steak and cook to desired doneness, about ~{5-7%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Once garlic is done, carefully transfer to a cutting board and mash with a fork
until smooth.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for steak over
medium-high heat. Add garlic (start with half and add more if desired); cook
for ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @beef demi-glace{1%unit} and @water{1/4%cup} (1⁄3 cup
for 4). Simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn off heat.

Stir in another @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4) and any resting juices from
steak until melted and combined. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice steak against the grain.

Divide mashed potatoes, Brussels sprouts, and steak between plates. Top steak and
mashed potatoes with sauce. Garnish with remaining chives and serve.